          <h3>HTML Document Structure</h3>
          <div class="all-explore">
            <h4>&rarr; Let's we see actually how does look a structure of html.</h4>
            <div class="explore">
              <p>HTML document structure describes by some different set of tags. And these tags contain some text and
                document. Also these tags are open with &lt; and closed with &gt; angle braces.Tags are some text
                enclosed within &lt; &gt; angle braces. The below text-images shows how the HTML document structure
                looks;</p>
              <img src="structure1.png" alt="structure"
                style="margin:2rem 0rem; width:119rem; border-radius: 1rem; box-shadow: 0rem 0rem 1rem 0rem gray;">
              <p>I think this is your first experience with this language so don't be discouraged because by the end of
                this course I assure you will have passed in this language. And i hope this course will helpfull for
                each and everyone.</p>
              <br>
              <p style="color:rgb(50, 50, 50); font-weight: bold;">We will study all the header and body tags in
                subsequent, but for now let's see what
                is HTML-document declaration tags like - &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;, &lt;html&gt;, &lt;head&gt;,
                &lt;title&gt;, &lt;body&gt;.
              </p>

              <h4 style="border:0.5rem solid gray; padding: 0rem 2rem; margin:2rem 0rem 0rem 0rem;">1. &lt;!DOCTYPE
                html&gt;</h4>
              <p>The &lt;!DOCTYPE&gt; declaration tag is used by the web browser to understand the version of
                the HTML used in the document. There are many other declaration types which can be used in HTML document
                depending on
                what version of HTML is being used. We will see more details on this while discussing
                &lt;!DOCTYPE...&gt; tag along with other HTML tags.</p>

              <h4 style="border:0.5rem solid gray; padding: 0rem 2rem; margin:2rem 0rem 0rem 0rem;">2. &lt;html&gt;</h4>
              <p>&lt;html&gt; tags are the keywords on a web page that define how your web browser must format and
                display your web page. Almost all tags contain two parts, an opening &lt;html&gt;, and a closing tag
                &lt;html/&gt;.</p>

              <h4 style="border:0.5rem solid gray; padding: 0rem 2rem; margin:2rem 0rem 0rem 0rem;">3. &lt;head&gt;</h4>
              <p>The &lt;head&gt; element is a container for metadata (data about data) and is placed between the
                &lt;html&gt; tag and the &lt;body&gt; tag. Metadata is data about the HTML document. Metadata is not
                displayed.</p>

              <h4 style="border:0.5rem solid gray; padding: 0rem 2rem; margin:2rem 0rem 0rem 0rem;">4. &lt;title&gt;
              </h4>
              <p>The &lt;title&gt; tag defines the title of the document or webpage. The title must be text-only, and it
                is shown in the browser's title bar on the top or in the page's tab. The &lt;title&gt; tag is required
                in HTML documents! The contents of a page title is very important for search engine optimization (SEO)!
              </p>

              <h4 style="border:0.5rem solid gray; padding: 0rem 2rem; margin:2rem 0rem 0rem 0rem;">5. &lt;body&gt;</h4>
              <p>The body tag can contain text content, paragraphs, headings, images, tables, links, audioes, gif,
                videos, etc. The &lt;body&gt; must be the second element after the &lt;head&gt; tag or it should be
                placed between &lt;head&gt; and &lt;html&gt; tags. This tag is required for every HTML document and
                should only use once in the whole HTML document.</p>
              <br>
              <br>
              <p>So these tages must have compulsory present on the html page.</p>
